<paragraph id="805736ABFF85FE4AFE06A291F9F8F8A6" blockId="1.[340,1660,169,2369]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">
The infuscation on the third antennal joint is not as deep as in the male, but in 
<specimenCount id="96EEFD22FF85FE4AFE46A2C9FD10FA67" box="[472,719,1477,1517]" count="2" pageId="1" pageNumber="88" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
it is even more so. 
<emphasis id="B29CEAB9FF85FE4AFBDCA2C9FB43FA67" box="[1090,1180,1477,1517]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Eyes:</emphasis>
not inflated above. 
<emphasis id="B29CEAB9FF85FE4AF997A2C9F9AAFA67" box="[1545,1653,1477,1517]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Frons:</emphasis>
narrowed gradually; clothed with hair laterally and above, and golden tomentum laterally, leaving a broad shining black, median stripe from the tubercle to the upper shining black portion of the frons. 
<emphasis id="B29CEAB9FF85FE4AFBEBA136FB33F9EF" box="[1141,1260,1594,1637]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Vertex:</emphasis>
black, with azure blue reflections (this is more pronounced in some specimens than others); clothed with black hair. 
<emphasis id="B29CEAB9FF85FE4AFD18A181FD2EF93F" box="[646,753,1677,1717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Ocelli:</emphasis>
equidistant. 
<emphasis id="B29CEAB9FF85FE4AFC7BA181FBB0F93F" box="[997,1135,1677,1717]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Occiput:</emphasis>
with a narrow margin visible above, clothed with fine yellowish tomentum. The transverse abdominal bands are blacker, rather wider, and better defined than in the male. 
<emphasis id="B29CEAB9FF85FE4AF9B7A1D1FE0BF8A6" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">Ovipositor:</emphasis>
short, yellow. In other respects the female is similar to the male
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="805736ABFF85FE4AF9B5A009F9EDF8A6" blockId="1.[340,1660,169,2369]" box="[1579,1586,1797,1836]" pageId="1" pageNumber="88">.</paragraph>
